snippet: A granite-and-iron-spot-brick townhouse, with terra-cotta embellishments and distinctive millwork inside, is poised to enter the market at $29 million.
abstract: Five-story, 20-foot-wide townhouse, in historic district on West 71st mid-block between Central Park West and Columbus Avenue, is set to enter market at $29 million; if 1892 structure is sold at asking price, it will set a neighborhood record for second time.
lead_paragraph: A granite-and-iron-spot-brick townhouse, with terra-cotta embellishments and distinctive millwork inside, is poised to enter the market at $29 million.

headline.main: Upper West Side Townhouse for $29 Million
